<p><strong>Debiasing Variational Autoencoder (DB-VAE):</strong> DB-VAE is a powerful framework for addressing algorithmic bias. It leverages variational autoencoders (VAEs) to learn a latent representation that separates sensitive attributes from other features. By disentangling these attributes, DB-VAE can mitigate bias and promote fairness in AI decision-making.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>DB-VAE Mathematics:</strong> We explore the mathematical foundations of DB-VAE, diving into the architecture, loss functions, and training procedures. Understanding the inner workings of DB-VAE empowers us to implement and apply this debiasing technique effectively.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

